request.description:
When retrieving a resources multiple times a rate limiting should be triggered at one to not come to the point where the system resources are depleted.

Don't be confused by the test result since every successfull request will result in a test result error since only 429 statuscode is tested for rate limiting.

So that means if there are some pass results the Rate limiting works since 429 is returned.

This was tested with 50 iterations and a rate limit of 10 requests per second.

This is an example of a nginx config with rate limit

```
http {

  limit_req_zone $binary_remote_addr zone=ratelimit:1m rate=10r/s;
  limit_req_status 429;

  server {
    listen 80;

    location / {
      limit_req zone=ratelimit;
      proxy_pass http://hapi-fhir-jpaserver-start:8080/;
      proxy_set_header X-Real-IP $remote_addr;
      proxy_set_header X-Forwarded-For $proxy_add_x_forwarded_for;
      proxy_set_header X-Forwarded-Proto $scheme;
      proxy_set_header   Host $http_host;
    }


  }
}

```

item.description:
When accessing or changing data HTTPS should be used with TLS Version of at least 1.2.

The following three requests are checking TLS versions.

The 1.0 should fail if you have configured the server to use >= 1.2

The 1.1 should fail if you have configured the server to use >= 1.2

The > 1.2 should be sucessfull if you have configured the server to use >= 1.2

Following nginx configuration is an example for setting the tls versions

```
server {
    listen 443 ssl;
    ssl_certificate     /etc/nginx/localhost.crt;
    ssl_certificate_key /etc/nginx/localhost.key;

    ssl_protocols TLSv1.2 TLSv1.3;

    location / {
      limit_req zone=ratelimit;
      proxy_pass http://hapi-fhir-jpaserver-start:8080/;
      proxy_set_header X-Real-IP $remote_addr;
      proxy_set_header X-Forwarded-For $proxy_add_x_forwarded_for;
      proxy_set_header X-Forwarded-Proto $scheme;
      proxy_set_header   Host $http_host;
    } 
  }

```
